********************************************************************
NOTE!                       HOW TO USE THE MS-DOS EDITOR WITH DESIRE
********************************************************************

Type "ed" instead of "edit" to substitute the MS-DOS editor (edit)
for dedit.com. This editor has mouse operations, nice menus and help
displays, and it lets you change its display colors.  But you must
explicitly "save" and "exit", while dedit does both in one operation.

"ed" calls the batch file dedit.bat, which currently reads

                \dos\edit syspic.lst

This assumes that the MS-DOS editor is kept in your \DOS directory, as
is usually the case.  Note that you can edit dedit.bat to substitute
other editors!

If you want to use Function Key F9 (or the command "edit") to call a
different editor, simply erase or rename dedit.com, or move it to a
different directory.


